05453nam a22008535i 9783110598254DE-B159720180725125623.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||180725s2018    gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831105982547 a10.1515/97831105982542doi  a(DE-B1597)494432  a(OCoLC)1046623143  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aHIS0020002bisacsh 7aLIT0041902bisacsh 7aPHI0020002bisacsh00aHope in ancient literature, history, and art :bAncient Emotions I /cGeorge Kazantzidis, Dimos Spatharas. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2018] 4c©2018  a1 online resource (407 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTrends in Classics - Supplementary Volumes ;v6300tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tContents -- tΙntroductory: 'Hope', elpis, spes: Affective and Non-affective Expectancy -- tPart I: Elpis. 'Hope' in Greek Literature -- t"Poet of Hope": Elpis in Pindar / rJohnston, Alexandre -- tHope and Hopelessness in Euripides / rFisher, Nick -- tUp from Tragicomedy: The Growth of Hope in Greek Comedy / rSlater, Niall W. -- tThe Politics of Hopelessness: Thucydides and Aristophanes' Knights / rTsoumpra, Natalia -- tElpis as Emotion and Reason (Hope and Expectation) in Fifth-century Greek Historians / rLateiner, Donald -- tPart II: Spes. 'Hope' in Latin Literature -- tDeos speravi (Miles 1209): Hope and the Gods in Roman Comedy / rFulkerson, Laurel -- tuestras spes uritis: Hope and Empire in Virgil's Aeneid / rPaschalis, Michael -- tHope Dies Last at Tomis / rMichalopoulos, Andreas N. -- t'A Historian Utterly Without Hope': Literary Artistry and Narratives of Decline in Tacitus' Historiae I / rPapaioannou, Sophia -- tPart III: Scripts of 'Hope' in History, Art, and Inscriptions -- tHope and Slavery / rVlassopoulos, Kostas -- tVelleius Paterculus, the Adoptions of 4 CE, and the Spes Race / rStiles, Andrew -- tAgainst Hope? The Untimely elpis of Northern Barbarians / rLampinen, Antti -- tThe Face of Hope: Isolated Heads in South Italian Visual Culture / rHeuer, Keely Elizabeth -- tHope and the Sub-adult / rBobou, Olympia -- tElpis in the Greek Epigraphic Evidence, from Rational Expectation to Dependence from Authority / rChaniotis, Angelos -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex Rerum et Nominum -- tIndex Auctorum Antiquorum et Locorum -- tEpigraphic and papyrological sources  aAlthough ancient hope has attracted much scholarly attention in the past, this is the first book-length discussion of the topic. The introduction offers a systematic discussion of the semantics of Greek elpis and Latin spes and addresses the difficult question of whether hope -ancient and modern- is an emotion. On the other hand, the 16 contributions deal with specific aspects of hope in Greek and Latin literature, history and art, including Pindar's poetry, Greek tragedy, Thucydides, Virgil's epic and Tacitus' Historiae. The volume also explores from a historical perspective the hopes of slaves in antiquity, the importance of hope for the enhancement of stereotypes about the barbarians, and the depiction of hope in visual culture, providing thereby a useful tool not only for classicist but also for philosophers, cultural historians and political scientists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Jul 2018) 4aAntike. 4aEmotion. 4aHoffnung. 4aantiquity. 4aemotions. 4aexpectation. 4ahope.1 aKazantzidis, George, eeditor.1 aSpatharas, Dimos, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2018 Englishz978311060400908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2018z978